The Reserve Bank of Australia
increased the significance of the Chinese yuan in its trade-
weighted index for the Australian dollar.  The yuan will account for 22.54 percent of the gauge as of
tomorrow, from 18.56 percent, the Sydney-based RBA said today on
its website. The Japanese yenâ€™s weighting will decline to 14.94
percent from 17.12 percent, while the euro will fall to 9.92
